OL,3,CWoman who killed pensioner in Co-op
OL,4,Cwas 'not being medicated' for psychosis
OL,6,FMr Rees lived in the nearby village of
OL,7,FTrealaw with his wife Eunice, who was
OL,8,Fwaiting for him in their car outside
OL,9,Fduring the attack.
OL,11,FToday, recording a narrative verdict,
OL,12,Fthe coroner concluded that Zara
OL,13,FRadcliffe was "suffering from
OL,14,Fpsychosis which was unmedicated and
OL,15,Fnot being assessed or managed at the
OL,16,Ftime approximate to events leading to
OL,17,Fhis death".
OL,19,FThe coroner also said John Rees was
OL,20,F"unlawfully killed".
